<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-11-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-11-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="1700" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1700">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 834.00/115.</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Montevideo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-11-23">
                                    <hi rend="italic">November 23, 1911</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Another customary revolution is on, led by Gondra and Schaerer, who, in
                            Europe, have secured two small vessels, rifles, artillery, ammunition.
                            Jara is believed to be with the Government.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Grevstad.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
